caption: Amazing, everything that you expect from a top notch chef. This is an upper class restaurant, everyone was dressed in suits and ties....but they still let me in with my family. I was dresses in shorts and flip flops. I did get some strange looks but hey, I'm used to being the center if attention. I had the rabbit and frog legs. So delicious. The atmosphere and staff were out if this world. Try the cheese tray appetizer. Paired with a good wine. You won't be disappointed.

This restaurant was wonderful until my bestfriend left the restaurant in tears because their were other people in the restaurant making fun of her dress and talking trash to her making her feel uncomfortable on her birthday . I’m sorry but this establishment being as nice as it is should do better and making others feel comfortable. The fact that the staff sat back and watched as a couple pointed and laughed at her till she was in tears and said nothing. This is a quick way to loose business now knowing that I and my friends will not be comfortable their. It’s really sad how some people can be so cruel
My favorite restaurant in the city! Always amazing service and food. No visit to New Orleans is complete without a stop here. You won't regret it!

I was able to bring my mom on her first ever visit to New Orleans during Mardi Gras and took her her. Going to one of Emeril’s restaurants as a dream of hers for years. She was excited and loved all the food and drinks. I’m thankful for the awesome staff that work there. They prepared amazing food and answered her questions with no problems.
NOLA Mardi Gras, three weeks ago. Oh my, quite the shocking change in such a short time
The place is very nice, excellent atmosphere and service. What gives it -1⭐is that all the food was very salty. Less salt = +1 ⭐ next time ;)

It genuinely looks like a very nice place, but our food just wasn't very good. One entree was very salty, the other - extremely salty. To the point where it completely kills the taste of the ingredients and you just want to wash it down with generous amounts of that $50 Chard are move on. There's nothing wrong with some salt, particularly when it comes to seafood, but you need at least something to balance the saltiness, and this was well off balance on both counts.  The baked oysters were fine, but they were chopped and baked to the point where almost anything would taste good if you put some creole spice on it. Solid appetizer, but not a culinary highlight.  Surely we could've just sent back whatever we didn't like, and ultimately get a very nice meal, but there are certain expectations of consistency that come with higher price tags, and these weren't met this time.
This place is amazing. Food is wonderful I got the filet and it was cooked to perfection. The crabmeat appetizer is outstanding. And complimentary champagne and caviiar!
Food and staff were excellent.
delicious
Great food, great service!
I love this place. Been there each time I’ve taken a trip to new Orleans and haven’t been disappointed.
Excellent meal and fabulous service

AMAZING! Honestly, I didn't have high expectations because I figured the place would be overhyped. It was not! Every single dish was  outstanding! We had a large party so we ordered quite a few things and shared. You honestly can't go wrong with anything you choose!
Salmon was excellent as well as the pasta. Would recommend this place to any of my friend's.
Amazing
Outstanding meal. First class service.

Dave's is my favorite Nashville style chicken in LA! always order mild because that's what I prefer. However I've tried the medium and hot. Medium has a perfect kick and the hot is also delicious if you can handle the heat! I'm a constant customer and always happy. The service is excellent and staff is always friendly. It's very clean in the restaurant. There is easy access parking on the lot. Definitely worth the wait.
Authentic Italian restaurant I love there spaghetti with meatballs, lasagna with cream of mushrooms so delicious.

A very elegant place to enjoy the delicious food.  The personal serving are outstanding  and noteworthy. The persons working is of good quality especially when it comes take care of the customers . I highly recommend  this restaurant to all

Made reservations weeks before Valentine's Day.  Ended up getting escorted through the kitchen to a back room with windows that overlooked an inner courtyard that literally had rat traps clearly visible.  Service was slow as hell.  The food was good, but not worth the price.  We live within walking distance, and with all the great choices in NOLA, we will not be back.
Really nice happy hour. Half price drinks and cheap small plates. Our group had a good time and we'll be back. FYI, I have not had dinner here so no opinion on that.
I've been here many times, best Steaks I've ever tasted. I also saw Bill Walton here once. Throw it down Big Man!!

Great experience, food was delish, and the staff was fantastic! Highly recommend this place. We enjoyed Thanksgiving dinner here and had a wonderful time. The atmosphere is very nice and comfortable too. We ate so much we couldn't walk after!

We were seated upstairs, in retrospect I should've requested during my reservation the first floor as we couldn't enjoy the piano player upstairs. The food was great the ribeye just about melted in your mouth, it was perfect! Loved the tableside presentation of Bananas Foster. The service from everyone...on point!👍🏼

Maybe one of my favorite gems in this area. Home made pasta. Friendly staff and most importantly tasty food. Their service lacks at times with how quick they get water or even how quick they come to you. Besides that I would choose to go here any day of the week due to the actual taste of food.
For the quality of food, the prices are very reasonable!  The food itself is very tasty. Service was superb!
Great customer service and food was tasty...
Upscale yes, good food yes, probably one of Emeril's best restaurants

The wife had the filet with mashed and I had the bone in rib eye with Lyonaise potatoes. She says its probably the best fillet she has ever had and it did have better flavor the my rib eye. First off I have never had lyonaise potatoes that were basically potato chips. I have always had them served almost like American fries but thinner. Unfortunately these were like eating stale, cold chips. My main issue was that my steak tasted like a salt lick. It was over salted towards the middle- but oh well maybe it was just me. The BBQ jumbo shrimp was out of this world and the service was certainly second to none. I have had dry aged steaks at some of the most prestigious restaurants and it was just a shame that I had to keep drinking water to finish it. I would definitely go again but I would have a different order. Honestly the service and wonderful flavors of the rest of the food saved this from being a 2 star review.

I cannot say enough good things about this restaurant. The waiter made the perfect recommendations for dinner and dessert. The service was phenomenal. The food was outstanding. You need to try this place!
Wonderful experience overall. Food was perfect, drinks were excellent, environment was all class.
We love their incredible food and the customer service is always top notch.
Not quite what I expected. The food is good, the presentations are ok, and the service is absolutely stellar.
Great atmosphere n food was delicious thank you for a wonderful evening
Food very good and excellent  service. Too loud. Crowded. Tourist place.
Always the best, my fav in NOLA!

Went to Delmonico’s for my 60th birthday celebration.  Had a party of 6.  Everything was off from the get go.  They put us in a table that was actually too big for our party - I felt like it was difficult to talk to the people at the table as we were so far apart.  Then, I felt somewhat rushed to order - which was so ironic because it took FOREVER - to get our main course.  Our reservation was at 7 - our food did not arrive until 9!!  2 hours?  When we complained - they looked at us like we were unreasonable and provided lame excuses while we watched other people come, eat  and go. Two people had steak, 3 had fish and one had a bowl of gumbo.  They also forgot some things we ordered and some items were actually cold.  As a way to say sorry - they sent out some lemoncello (? Not sure of the spelling) which was lame as we had two non drinkers at the table.  Hard to say if the food was actually good because the experience was pretty darn awful.  $500 down the drain.  Expected to pay that but didn’t expect the experience to be so BAD.  Overrated.
We enjoyed our lunch.  The food and service were both excellent.
The experience was absolutely devine. The food was delicious. The service was excellent. I would definitely recommend this to who ever comes to New Orleans.
Great food. Zory was great. Vern took very good care of us.  Piano bar was a plus.
This is not even close to the old Delmonico’s quality.  The only thing sadder then my wallet, is their bread pudding.  Much better options in New Orleans for this kind of money

Went here for a private event.  The space was really nice, you get to go through the kitchen to get to the private dining room.  They start with cornbread that was buttery and pretty standard.  I got the shrimp and grits, some of my shrimp were overcooked and got rubbery and the grits cake wasn't anything to rave about, but the buttery sauce was delicious.  I ended up using the cornbread to soak up the sauce.  The salad was a pretty good size portion, almost there size of a lunch entree salad.  I got the drum fish, it was cooked very well and the artichokes were a nice addition to the dish.  I was so full that I took my dessert to go and have yet to taste it but it looked delicious and my fellow diners are their all up.
Flavors were beautifully put together for the small plate pork cheek and steak tartare.  Excellent service and welcoming atmosphere

We only got into the happy hour menu, but by the time we had gotten thru tasting half of them we had decided to try the rest and skip the main menu. Alas , we missed a number of wonderful things I would love to have tried,  but we dont think we missed anything.  We just left our selves needing another shot.  We sat at the bar and tried a couple of the specials and local beers with great attention from the bar tender. I guess you can say you would not expect less. Please go and enjoy.

Excellent food and service.  We didn't sit at the regular table, but decided to sit at the bar and enjoy their wonderful $.99 chargrilled oysters & half priced cocktails during happy hour to start.  Many of the other places that do chargrilled oysters usually grill it so much the oysters are all shriveled up and you barely get to taste them, but not here at Delmonico's. The oysters were perfectly grilled and seasoned.  The bartenders also know how to make some great cocktails here.  After eating a dozen oysters and some snacks, we ended up splitting the Kansas City strip steak, and it was delicious.  It's one of the best steaks I've had in a while - perfectly cooked and seasoned to medium rare. They also bring you a bevy of sauces for the steak, but there's no need. It's perfect as is.  Because we sat in the bar area, I thought the service wouldn't be as good as if we had sat at the tables, but I was wrong.  The service was very attentive, friendly, and fast even though it was pretty busy.  Another one of Emeril's establishment that doesn't disappoint. We'll definitely be back.

Excellent venue for an exquisite dinner. We were thrilled with our meals. The place is a little upscale. The service is wonderful and the atmosphere is cozy and comfortable. We were very happy with everything. If you are looking for enjoyment and great food then  we recommend this restaurant.
Loved everything  about the food and service

Dinner was excellent as was the serving staff.  Had the Maine lobster gnocchi with trumpet mushrooms and a saffron cream sauce.  We ordered a 21 day dry aged NY strip steak and was very surprised at the flavor this steak had.  I thought Doris Metropolitan had the monopoly on dry aged steaks, but this steak would give theirs a run for their money.  The mashed potatoes and spinach were good, but the star was the steak.
Excellent service. Fun bartender. Food was all good but did not meet expectations or match price.

Wow! What a great meal! And a fabulous way to celebrate Thanksgiving!! The filet Oscar was perfect and the brussel sprouts and super buttery mashed potatoes really hit the spot! Service was impeccable.
Always a great time
The food excellent as well as the service.
Came for happy hour and had a great experience.... restraurant seating at this place is a little more high class for my taste. Charbroiled oyster special was amazing and had great drinks.
Food, amazing. Ambience just ok.
All good except very slow to serve.
Love this place. Eat there everytime I visit NOLA

Bamboo straws The interior was beautiful the chandeliers were amazing the furniture was very comfortable. The price's were much lower than they should have been. The lighting set the mood perfectly. The sevice was amazing the food came very quickly and there was completairy caviar and the most amazing corn bread.

One of the best meals I’ve been ever had. We had a large group, twelve, and dined in the crystal room. It’s beautifully decorated with a grand chandelier and view of the wine room. The menu was pretty impeccably designed, excellent variety of starters and entrees. We ordered starters family style, individual entrees, and a few orders of duck to taste. Aside from the food being superb the entire staff was welcoming even to some of my hedonistic friends. All in all an excellent place to have a great dining experience or a big dinner with you best friends.
Thank you Lloyd. Fabulous wait staff. Very professional.
I had a dry aged ribeye, which was excellent. Great bourbon and wine list.
So delicious! I wish I can eat here daily.

I love the pecan pie with praline crumble. I ordered the lobster gnocchi and I found the flavor profile to be rich and over seasoned. For the entree I ordered the lobster stuffed flounder, and the flounder was dry from overcooking. The stuffing had excellent flavor with generous lobster pieces!

Amazing food, great service and a comfortable classy environment! We’ve eaten here twice now and both times it has exceeded our expectations. The Ribeye was THE BEST we’ve ever had. Also a great place to try the Pappy Van Winkle 23 year. It was pricey but worth it!
Our waiter was fantastic!. Incredible food. Really enjoyed watching him make the Bananas Foster

A $240 meal that was thoroughly disappointing. You're obviously paying for the name. Our wagyu steaks were not as tender as expected. The lyonnaise potatoes had more onion than potato. The collard greens were flavorless. The pecan pie wasn't even warm. Service was mediocre and to top it off, the bathroom was dirty!
WOW! Had an amazing steak! Service was the best in town.

Booked a reservation at Emeril’s Delmonico on Open Table for a romantic dinner and had the best meal I’ve ever eaten.  I ordered the Redfish which was mind-blowingly incredible.  Starters included lobster ravioli, polenta and yummy corn bread.  My husband had the bone-in ribeye and scallops and thought it was great.  The banana's foster is so good!  The atmosphere is elegant and refined without being stodgy.  Dress smart casual and you will fit right in.  We will return here on our next visit to New Orleans.
Food was awesome and the service was exceptional.

Went here late night (9pm), sat at the bar and love the service! Like the steak tartare. Like the cornbread that comes with the soup:) cheese plate is good and can have a try (but I’d prefer bread to grilled bread). Oyster is a bit southern. -I didn’t try the entries and so far the prices are very reasonable. Haven’t tried enough creole cuisines so really have nothing to say about comparisons. -its quality is worth 5 star, yet among the similarity priced restaurants it is a 4.2 star - a “match” to its price
Excellent place for streak in New Orleans. Took the family for a birthday celebration. Service was phenomenal. I couldn't ask for any better food. Best restaurant to eat at in my opinion.
Excellent Food,Excellent Service,Wonder Atmosphere...
Love it

Where do I begin...Kenny, Cory, Seth one more guy with long dreds well kept in a ponytail...that's where it begins and ends! They were SPOT ON! Everything Kenny recommended we got and LOVED. So much oohing and awe-ing! Just check out the picks and see! Great atmosphere and fun! We will be back!

Food was great but it was absolutely freezing inside. The meal took well over 2 hours and I had goosebumps the entire time. I had to leave my party twice to go warm up outside, joined by another women a few moments later who too needed to dethaw. If people are expected to sit and dine for that long the temperature needs to be comfortable.
Absolutely amazing!

The food was amazing! Everything we had was awesome. We had the wild boar with sweet potato gnocchi as the appetizer and I had the chicken for entree and my partner had the ribeye. It was so good. The food just melts in your mouth. We would definitely come back.
Best food I have ever eaten!!!

Nice atmosphere and very friendly staff. There’s a massive wine selection and good menu. A few misses of the night was the luke warm food and after ordering the bananas foster we were informed that they ran out of vanilla ice cream. They did substitute it with another kind but it just wasn’t the same. I’m not sure how you run out of a main ingredient for such a traditional dish
Fantastic
Precisely Extravagant!!! Every single thing was carried out with care and attention to every detail Simply out, one of the best meals of my life!

My wife and I came to New Orleans for our anniversary and we tried many restaurants at recommendations from various friends and acquaintances. Emeril's Delmonico salvaged an otherwise disappointing food experience. The service was outstanding and the food was graciously exquisite.
no hats policy is dumb.
Only treat you right if you are hollywood status. 0/0 would recommend. Food is equal to kid cuisine or hungryman
Flawless keep up very well considering how busy they were and our party of 12
The food and the service was impeccable!  Gotta try the bbq shrimp and make sure you dip the bread in your sauce! Laissez les bon temps rouler!!!
This is a great place for a special meal. Start during happy hour for half price drinks and $5 small plates. Then took our wine to the dining room for an amazing meal!
Amazing
Stopped for happy hour everything we had was awesome
My second visit in a month.
Service was impeccable, as expected. Food was outstanding. We had the filet and the aged ribeye. The flavor was amazing and along with the house made Worcestershire, it doesn't get much better.

Wonderful the staff was amazing the food perfect and I appreciate it because this was my niece's first 5 star dining experience. We went early for happy hour. The bar tender was fun and skilled.  We had several of their sides and appetizers.   Our duck entee and porkchop entree were exactly as.ordered. her porkchop was seasoned to perfection my sauces for.the duck delicious. Our bill was high, two people could have a nice dinner for half of what we paid, but we had a blast and a full bag of leftovers. Bon appetit!  This is a must do restaurant not an emperor's new clothes.  This man can cook!
Staff was outstanding. Excellent food great way to spend my last evening in New Orleans

Do yourself a favor and visit Delmonico’s. I’ve eaten at several of Emeril’s restaurants and this, by far is my favorite. The atmosphere is intimate, the service is unbeatable, the food prepared for us by Chef Michael was absolutely delicious. This place is worth every penny. Don’t forget to top off this 5 star meal with the Bananas Foster prepared at table side.

Delmonico's is one of our top three favorite restaurants in the city. We were hesitant to eat here previously since we thought it was a steakhouse.  While eating at Merils one of our favorite restaurants in the city the manager Jeremy recommended we go to Delmonico's and told us about all of the other dishes in addition to to steak  that they.  Our first visit was with close friends and we had two different fish dishes which were fantastic. The almondine fish preparation is by far the top prepared almondine in the city.  In the same week we were delighted to go back with a group of about 8 people from out of town.  Several friends ordered different types of steaks and indicated they were the best steaks they had had in the city and possibly the country! I tried the duck breast with the Madeira sauce which is also a top dish.  On both visits we had a variety of cocktails which were superb as well as extensive wine selections.  Be sure sometime during your meal to ask for one or two of the housemaid liquors.  The service is top-notch and the staff is extremely friendly and a joy to dine with.  As locals we eat out several times a week and now Delmonico's is a place we will frequent together as well as with our family.  Wethet you are local or an  out-of-towner Delmonico's is a must meal!
like it allot
Outstanding food and service. Quail was amazing and the bananas foster to die for!
Best restaurant experience
Awesome food and service and atmosphere. The sheepshead is amazing. The duck was a little to gamey but the desserts are spectacular.
Food was FANTASTIC and the service was good
Amazing food and spectacular service. Best food in New Orleans!
Excellent
Wonderful service, great atmosphere, excellent food

We haven't been NO for quite a while and we wanted to relive some of the delights we experienced before. Emeril's Delmonico lived up to what we remembered. Food, service and wine all were excellent. Their grilled oysters we astounding.
The food was mildly seasoned and overpriced. The restaurant needs an update. The carpet was filthy.
Excellent food and service.  Highly recommend it!
Service and food was a true Nola treat. I couldn't have asked for a better dining experience.

Best filet mignon / cornbread / macaroni pie/ sweet potatoes / mash potatoes / specialty cocktails & deserts to date! Next time I’ll take photos; too busy enjoying good food & a wonderful time. Did I mention the live pianist !? LawdaMercy. On street / Valet parking. Walk-in, but I recommend calling ahead. The service made you feel right at home, on an Easter Sunday after church. Fine dining yet I was welcomed in and felt very comfortable ! Much love ^_^  This gem of a restaurant is highly recommended!
The staff was excellent unfortunately the food was subpar. You are being overcharged for a name basically. The best dishes were the appetizers in my opinion.
It was nice
Great food and very good old fashioned cocktail.
I was a little disappointed with the chef's work. The service was great. But the steak wasn't particularly flavorful. The drinks and desserts were impeccable.
Everything was dabulous- food, service, drinks and atmosphere
Service and food were impeccable!

Absolutely  the best meal I've  had in New Orleans  in 2 years. Duck #1, steak....none better. Did the 3 for $17 apps outstanding....brussel sprouts and spinach for sides! No room for dessert and that was upsetting  because the bananas foster looked and smelled like heaven. I don't hi I've 5 stars many times but this place would get 6 if it was an option!!
Ver few restaurants I enjoy as much as Delmonico's.   Service is impeccable and the food it amazing!  It's our go to place!!!
Wow! Best restaurant in New Orleans
Amazing food the service was amazing perfect date night experience.  Highly recommend.
The food was very flavorful. Wait staff were proffinal and friendly  .great experience
Food was excellent. Service was excellent. Will definitely be back!
Well ?!?!!! You should bring mother  just because you owe it to her!!!
(Translated by Google) Impeccable service  (Original) Impeccable service

Everything was delicious from the unique take on boudin appetizers to the flavorful entrees, desserts, and drinks. Of course, I would expect no less from Emeril!  Ambiance was cozy and romantic, and service was on point - from the parking lot attendant to reception and wait staff.  My Cajun companion and I both loved everything about Delmonico - even with him being a very tough critic when it comes to local cuisine!  Highly recommend for locals and tourists and can't wait to visit again.  Thanks so much for a very special birthday! #NuttieFoodie #Birthday  #locals #tourists #dinner #reviews
Excellent, coordinated service, and good portions to eat up, and a creative and simple menu to taste it all
Vernon and his staff is the best I go anytime I can.  Best service in new Orleans
Was great food and atmosphere. Service was top notch and some of the best food I have ever ate.
Food and service was phenomenal!!!!

This was my second time to visit Emeril's Delmonico for their daily Happy Hour which runs from 5-7 pm. Why I didn't review this fantastic and tasty deal after my first visit, I don't know. This time I took a friend along and we ordered one of each item on their $5 menu as well as six of their 99 cent chargrilled oysters. Even the french fries with garlic aioli were delicious! In addition to the $5 small plates, their wines by the glass and inventive specialty cocktails are half priced.  Do yourself a favor and check out this very tasty deal!
Our dinning experience was good but our trip to the bar was not.  The bartender was abrupt and rude.  Really soured our evening.

This was a good dining experience. Warm and welcoming greeting upon entrance. Wait staff very attentive to customer. The food was delicious.  We had barbecue shrimp. They have cornbread to eat with it if you want to. Soooooo good. Used cornbread to dip in sauce.  We also enjoyed the iceberg lettuce salad.  I had Quail Clemenceau which was seasoned and cooked perfectly. My husband had Louisiana Drum Amandine which he enjoyed. Excellent food.

So disappointed.   We brought my foodie son to New Orleans for the first time and he couldn't wait for Emeril's Delmonico.  He checked the menu online and was very excited to go.  I do have to say that the waitstaff was good; highly attentive.   The crab dip appetizer was delicious and we thought we had made the right choice.  My son ordered the bone in strip steak.  It was very fatty (not rendered, white fat) and tough.  I ordered the pork chop.  It was pretty dry.  The string beans were good.  My husband ordered the lobster pasta.  The pasta and gravy were good.  The lobster tail was overcooked and chewy.   We ordered the mac and cheese, dirty rice and lyoinnaise potatoe sides.  Mac and cheese sauce had separated and was very oily.  The potatoes were dry and like semi soggy potato chips.  The dirty rice was ok but, as others have said, very salty.  All in all, we won't return and cannot reccomend to others.

Came in for happy hour and was greeted by a gorgeous bartender named Brandi. She recommended some tremendously delicious dishes on the happy hour menu. We sampled several appetizers. I recommend the charbroiled oysters, crispy pork cheek, deviled eggs & shrimp and corn beignets. Thanks! We’ll be back!
Great food, service and happy hour everyday!
Nothing to wrote home about. Overpriced and basic. So many other lively places to eat in Nola.
The food was spectacular and the service was impeccable. If you ever have the opportunity I strongly suggest you visit.
Pretentious, Over the Top! Laughable! Not what food is about!
Amazing.

Royal Reds shrimp cocktail is to die for. Plantains were perfectly crisp. Cornbread that melts in your mouth. The Drum entre was of course delish. The atmosphere very comfortable. The noise  level was amazing low. Music very appropriate.  Very nice waiters.
Enjoyed a nice dessert here!

Ribeye steak was great. Too much pepper on the shaved brussels salad (couldn't eat) and turtle soup. Creme brulee was ok, but was like it was premade and refrigerated, best when heat top right before they bring to table. Wait staff was very attentive, but kept bumping our chairs.
Great place love Happy hour
VERY GOOD! I enjoyed my steak so much! The service was fantastic and it is such a beautiful restaurant.
Quite a lovely dining experience. The service was world class. Drinks top notch. My one gripe is the preponderance of land-based protein on the menu. Would love to have a few more seafood choices.
Great Food and Service
With out a doubt the very best restaurant in NOLA.  Please try it you will be delighted.
Exceptional as always.

4 Diamonds Restaurant 💎 but 5 stars ⭐️ Google!! Expect to be amazed. 😎  If you never come here and you want to have even a more VIP experience from what the restaurant already is, as for the private rooms. (Crystal room is the most exclusive one)  We had dinner at the Cypress room and everything was incredible. First of all they take you there crossing by the middle of the kitchen lol that was great. Once you get to the room, the attention from the waitress makes you feel comfortable and they are constantly taking care of you.  I had some starter don’t remember the name with some caviar on top (check my picture) and was a perfect combination of flavors! The rest also amazing, check all my entire photos and videos.
Food, ambiance, and service were all excellent.  Better than Emeril's New Orleans.
So good..the oysters made me cry when i but in my mouth..the steak was like butter

Pricey but worth every penny.  Amazing history,  food, and service!  Great spot for a romantic evening or special occasion.   Highly recommended for both locals and tourists alike.  Just dont look at the bill hand over the plastic and worry about that a different day don't bring down your amazing experience with prices at the end.
Very good but prefer Emeril's in the french quarter.

Delmonico was good, but nothing was a super standout. We were a party of 10 and it was a Sunday night so I will give them a bit of a pass, but overall it was just fine, which isn't what I would expect from a restaurant of this caliber.
Great food and service

This is Emeril lagasse's restaurant how could it be anything but spectacular.  Everyone was so kind and friendly.  we were early and I'm so glad we got to sit at the bar and the bartender was very personable chatted with us the whole time but never stopped working.  I had a drink here recommended it was one he had created it was so delicious.  The food was amazing The dessert was amazing. my waiter had made an error and forgot to bring me something and I told them it was fine he kept apologizing and he brought me her free dessert because of it.  this is a very small restaurant so make sure you make reservations.  My recommendation is to go there and have the entire experience.

Came here for my son’s birthday dinner with high expectations. We were very happy with the starters: bbq shrimp, crawfish & eggplant stuffed peppers and gumbo. They were delicious. The entries we ordered are:  •Nuts crusted flounder with artichoke & couscous and some very creamy rich flavor of green sauce. This is on special menu, waiter strong suggested it. Unfortunately, we didn’t enjoy this dish. The flounder is dry and flaky, the artichoke’s flavor is just not the right fit to this dish and the creamy green sauce is too creamy rich. This dish make us felt uncomfortably full.  • Paneerd pork chop. I wasn’t expecting that this is a breaded pork chop. I expected a nicely piece of grilled or pan fried meat, so I was very disappointed when it came breaded. However, the meat is very tender. I also don’t enjoy the dirty rice that came with the dish - I did not enjoy the character in it.  • lamb chop. The meat is big and thick and came with creamy quiche. We prefer smaller and more tender lamb chop. Again, this is a heavy dish.  Our conclusion is the starters are delicious, but the entries are very American style - big and rich but not having sophisticated flavor.
Good atmosphere, delicious food, excellent service!
Always a place I stop by when in town and never disappointed.

The servers made it extremely uncomfortable,  particularly Mike. He continually hit on this girl at my table after she had expressed she had a boyfriend. Sincerely one of the most awful dining experiences I have ever encountered. Hire better staff to ensure your guests feel comfortable.
It's was great, service was great

Very good but I could have probably done the same food at home for 1 quarter of the cost. Ambiance was nice, service was a little sketchy.  I'm a chef by trade so I dont think an average Joe would do so.
Food and service was superb. Very friendly, k knowledgeable and the menu choices wereexvellent
Another of Emeril's restaurant and a special place in new Orleans   the food was great, service extraordinary...
Amazing food and service plus we got a view of the parade when it was passing through the area.
Absolutely incredible. Service was excellent, food was exceptional. Highly recommend the bananas foster to finish off any meal

The happy hour 5-7 has 99 cent chargrilled oysters. Delicious!! Drinks are half priced as well as other starters. Compliments of the chef are the sweet potato chip with caviar and creme fraiche as well as the skillet of buttered cornbread and sparking wine. The entrees were the 21 day aged rib eye and collard greens. The steak was cook a perfect medium well and the greens tasted as though they were slow cooked all day with hammocks. The lobster I'berville was delicious and the lobster and pasta texture was perfect. One thing I would say is the sauce with the pasta was a little too buttery. The lemon thyme cheesecake is yum!! From the moment we were greeted and seated, everything was exquisite! We were presented with a small taste from the kitchen as we perused the massive wine list (we had to restrict our looking to Italian wines, just to help the decision-making process) and looked over the menu. We started with the carpaccio, which was presented to us by the manager - along with some of the most special corn bread my husband has ever tasted.  My husband had the gumbo - which he declared was the MVP, and the hostess said she would pass that on - and I, the beet salad. I ordered the lamb shank entree that separated cleanly from the bone with merely a tug of my fork. My husband had a rib eye steak that was perfectly prepared and presented with several sauces.  I left a lot on my plates, trying not to be a glutton, but eating for flavor is easy to do. The Barolo we selected was an excellent pairing to all our selections, the cappuccino was prepared beautifully. The chairs were also immensely comfortable. Everything is set for a dining experience that will take time to savor, and no expense has been spared to insure this. Kevin and the entire team who took care of us were professionals at the top of their game.

We made reservations and specified that it was for a birthday dinner. When we arrived, on time, the restaurant was almost empty, yet we were told to wait in the bar for our table to be ready. When we did get a table, within minutes, it was in the middle of the floor with the rest of the empty tables on all sides. This became a significant fact as the evening wore in, as the bevy of waiters consistently jostled my chair as they made their way around the gradually filling room.  We dressed for a fancy birthday evening, and the majority of the patrons were dressed as well, but there were jeans and hoodies in attendance. The food was delicious, and the rib eye was perhaps the most perfectly cooked medium rare that I've ever had. The pork chop and cream cheese mashed potatoes was delicious, and the guappo salad was very tasty. We were treated to a small glass of champagne and a sorbet for dessert to recognize our occasion, which was very thoughtful. I wish I could give it the five stars that I wanted the experience to be, but the atmosphere didn't match the expectations.

Oh my! That’s all I can think to say after eating here. Everything we ate and drank was ‘knock your socks off’ wonderful! The service was on par with the best restaurants I’ve been to, while not seeming too stuffy.  Favorite dish of the night? It’s hard to choose one. We had the crispy pork cheek, turtle soup, duck breast, lamb shank, and Brussels sprouts. For me, it’s a tie between the pork cheek and the lamb for my favorite dish of the night.  For dessert, we had the night’s special of bananas foster tiramisu. Not a combination you would think works, and one that isn’t immediately obvious even when eating it. But by the second bite you say “ah! I get it!”  I have to say, I wasn’t sure I would enjoy this as much as Paul Prudhomme, but I have to say I have a new favorite. Thank you, Delmonico, for an excellent evening!
